DataElement.preferredName: Qualitative Evaluation Percentage Automated Neuropsychological Assessment Metrics Accuracy Outcome java.lang.Long
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A type of evaluation that is primarily descriptive and interpretative, and may or may not lend itself to quantification. Mainly concerned with the properties, the state, and the character (i.e., the nature) of phenomena. It implies an emphasis on processes and meanings that are rigorously examined, but not measured in terms of quantity, amount, or frequency. (www.unfpa.org/monitoring/toolkit/glossary.pdf and Nonprofit Good Practice Guide Glossary)_A fraction or ratio with 100 understood as the denominator.:A computerized library of tests designed for baseline screening and serial assessment of neurocognitive function.:The quality of nearness to the truth or the true value.:A phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is a long integer (64-bit two's complement).
